<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900717-0045</DOCNO><DOCID>900717-0045.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- New Century Communications Inc.:   Company Approves a Plan   To Restructure Debt, Stock</HL><DATE>07/17/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4</SO><CO>   X.EDG GE</CO><IN>BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)</IN><LP>   The board of New Century Communications Inc., NewYork-based parent of trade-magazine publisher EdgellCommunications Inc., approved in principle a plan torestructure its $290 million of debt and $57 million ofpreferred stock.   New Century was formed through a December 1987 leveragedbuy-out of Harcourt Brace Jovanovich Inc.'sbusiness-publishing, trade-show production andschool-supplies distribution businesses. The buy-out wasexecuted by General Electric Co.'s investment-banksubsidiary, Kidder, Peabody and Co.; members of Edgell's seniormanagement; and others.</LP><TEXT>   &quot;Our objective is to be able to dedicate more operatingincome to the company,&quot; a spokeswoman for New Century said.The restructuring would cut and defer payments of interestand principal.   Advertising remains soft, but New Century's two otherdivisions are performing well, the spokeswoman said. Therestructuring is subject to negotiations with lenders andinvestors.   New Century said its senior lenders -- which include GE'sfinancial-services arm, General Electric Capital Corp., andseven banks -- have blocked it from making a $7 millionsemiannual interest payment, due yesterday on its 14% seniorsubordinated debentures, for as long as 120 days.</TEXT></DOC>